-- Gome Founder Huang Retains Global Law Firm Hogan Lovells, Newspaper Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-22T21:29:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/gome-founder-huang-retains-global-law-firm-hogan-lovells-newspaper-says.html
Huang Guangyu , imprisoned founder
of  Gome Electrical Appliances Holdings Ltd ., has retained
international law firm Hogan Lovells as he seeks to regain
control of the company, the South China Morning Post reported.   The firm was retained for Huang by his wife Du Juan and is
officially acting for family company Shinning Crown Holdings
Ltd., the Hong Kong-based English-language newspaper said today,
citing Hogan Lovells partner Neil McDonald.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  